ement of crops due to COVID 19 lockdown. The state govt. wants to assure farmers that every single grain of agricultural produce will be procured. From 15 April 2020, govt. will start of procurement of mustard and April 20 for the wheat crop. This announced extension in the last date of repayment of cooperative loans by farmers from April 15 till the procurement of their crops and he assured that no interest would be charged from them for the extended period.Doctors \u2013 The state govt. will provide ex-gratia amount for doctors performing duty on COVID-19 patients. These doctors will get Rs. 50 lakh from Rs. 10 lakh as announced earlier. Moreover, ex-gratia of Rs. 30 lakh would be given to nurses and Rs. 20 lakh for others.Lab Setup \u2013 CM said that 5 labs had already been setup in the state to test COVID 19 and 2 more would be setup very soon.Beds for Isolation \u2013 Haryana govt. has setup 2,500 beds for isolation of COVID 19 patients in the state. Moreover, around 6,500 beds have been setup to provide quarantine facility to suspected patients.Haryana COVID Relief Fund \u2013 CM Manohar Lal Khattar said that 5.84 crore had already been collected for the Haryana Covid Relief Fund. As many as 2,000 people had thus far contributed to it and more people are likely to contribute in the next few days.Mukhyamantri Parivar Samriddhi Yojana beneficiaries \u2013 Funds would be transferred to around 12.56 lakh people registered under the Mukhyamantri Parivaar Smridhi Yojna.Construction Workers \u2013 Around 3.85 lakh families registered under the Construction Labour Welfare Board would also be paid Rs. 1,000 per week as financial aid.References\u2014 Haryana Corona Relief Fund Account Number : 39234755902 IFSC : SBIN0001509 SBI, Sector \u2013 10, Panchkula \u2014 Total Count of Volunteers : 39345For more details, visit the official website at https://covidssharyana.in/  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now Source / Reference Link: https://covidssharyana.in/  at  "}